Text.string: I would handle this myself if it weren't for my oath. Believe it or not, I am forbidden from even slapping a mosquito that bites me! Woe is me for choosing the non-violent path! So you must slaughter in my stead, oh righteous gunslinger!
Oui! OUI! Disembowel them, my divine murderer! Splay their guts on the ground like intestinal confetti!
Oh, most glorious! Send that beast screaming into the void! Split its skull and drench this holy place in monstrous blood! Oui! Oui! The suffering is intoxicating!
Ouf! Sort of, uh, got caught up in the moment. Thank the six storms you came along when you did. When the Maliwan scourge is driven away, we will toast your divine bloodshed!

When we monks take the oath of non-violence, we must relinquish all our worldy weapons. They are stored nearby, and I urge you to take whatever you need from our weapon depository, my vivisecting avenger! Then return to me.

I admit I am conflicted by my part in your unhinged pursuit of violence. Yet, perhaps such transgressions are themselves the will of the storms. You have given me much to ponder, Vault Hunter. And much to drink. Salut! Truly, this is the happiest of hours!
At last, a favorable wind! I require your help!
It's an infestation!
A righteous slaughter! Now, you must find the final ratch hive and put an end to this infestation! Go, my blood-drenched champion, go! The massacre beckons!
You must come quickly! The Holy Distillery is infested with ratch! This way!
There we are. Now—inside, quickly! Before the ratch completely infest this holy place!
Yuck. More of that ratch gunk. Use the spirits to clear the way!
Woe is you! Another blockage of ratch gunk! Make use of the holy spirits to clear your path!
Yet more festering ratch gunk stands in your way! The holy spirits should take care of that!
It would appear that this monster has died of over-intoxication! Ah! Do me an additional favor and retrieve its liver!

You see, these pickled ratch livers are actually the secret ingredient behind our holy spirits. We keep a flock of ratch for this purpose, but they escaped their bonds and started running wild throughout the distillery!
Ah. Now that should come in handy once the infestation is cleared out.
Excellent! That pickled ratch liver will be very useful to me.
I shall make such a spirit with that ratch liver! Oui oui!
That ratch liver seems to be perfectly pickled for our purposes.
Grab that clapper and ring the bell of inebriation to summon me when you are ready! A reward is in order!
Ah, and I see you've gathered the pickled ratch livers I asked for! Très bien, très bien! An additional reward is in order!

Thank the six storms, my prayers are answered! I am Brother Mendel of the Impending Storm, sworn to an oath of non-violence. So, I must beg your assistance with these ferocious ratch! You must eradicate them for me!
Ah, that's... ratch gunk. Our distilled spirits should be strong enough to melt such things. Shoot the nearby cask and be rid of that foul infestation!
How I envy you, Vault Hunter. Unencumbered by the oath, unchained by morality. Hunt down those foul ratches, and rip the still-beating hearts from their wretched thoraxes!
